SUMMARY:Writing Our Future: Representation in YA
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20180923T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20180923T120000
UID:48505989721
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/writing-our-future-representation-
 in-ya-tickets-48505989721\n\nJoin Diaspora Dialogues at Word on the Street
  for a "Writing Our Future: Representation in YA" panel.\nAs a society\, i
 nstilling a love of reading and literature in children is deemed to be imp
 ortant. But more often than not\, the books available to young Canadians d
 ont have characters that look like them\, or storylines they can relate to
 .\nOn Sunday\, September 23\, 2018\, from 10 a.m. - 12 p.m.\, Diaspora Dia
 logues invites you to the Toronto Book Awards tent for a riveting conversa
 tion about the state of diversity in YA fiction\, the resulting impact on 
 children and society\, and the journeys of authors writers whove published
  books in the genre.\nFeaturing:\n\nAuthorAdwoa Badoe\nAuthorTanaz Bhathen
 a\nAuthorDavid A. Robertson\nTransatlantic Literary Agency'sAmy Tompkins\n
 Moderated by:Quill & Quire'sShanda Deziel\n\nSunday\, September 23 Toronto
  Book Awards Tent\, Harbourfront Centre 10 a.m. to 12 p.m.\nCost: Free\n\n
 \n
LOCATION:Harbourfront Centre\, 235 Queens Quay W\, Toronto\, ON M5J 2G8
URL:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/writing-our-future-representation-in-ya-ti
 ckets-48505989721
