DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20180526T170000
UID:45516089850
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/stories-from-the-six-dd-at-doors-o
 pen-tickets-45516089850\n\nJoin Diaspora Dialogues for a full day of event
 s at Doors Open\, including free screenings of movies\, interviews with di
 rectors and writers and more.\nProgram\n\n10 a.m. to 10:15 a.m. Introducti
 ons\n10:15 a.m. to 12 p.m.  Screening of David Bezmozgis' NATASHA\n12:00 p
 .m. to 12:15 p.m.  Break\n12:15 p.m. to 12:45 p.m.  Interview with actor G
 enadijs Dolganovs\, moderated by journalist Tina Hassannia.\n12:45 p.m. to
  1 p.m.  Break\n1 p.m. to 1:45 p.m.  Interview with videographer and edito
 rMoumy Mback\, moderated by DD's Miranda Newman.\n1:45 p.m. to 2 p.m.  Bre
 ak\n2 p.m. to 3 p.m.  Interview with writer and director Sharon Lewis by N
 OW's Chris Rattan\, and a behind-the-scenes look at the making of Brown Gi
 rl Begins\n3 p.m. to 3:15 p.m.  Break\n3:15 p.m. to 4:45 p.m.  "Writing To
 ronto On Screen" panel featuring writer and director Charles Officer\, fil
 mmaker Lu Asfaha\, cinematographer Marlon Paul and editor and director San
 jay Talreja.\n4:45 p.m. to 5 p.m.  Closing remarks\n\n\nPlease note: If yo
 u plan to attend the NATASHA screening\, email miranda@diasporadialogues.c
 om to reserve your seat.\nDD thanks Zoomer Media for hosting us as part of
  theirDoors Open programming. We'd also like to acknowledge Mongrel Media\
 , and our supporters\, the Canada Council for the Arts\, the Ontario Arts 
 Council\, the Ontario Trillium Foundation\, the Toronto Arts Council\, the
  Michael Decter Foundation\, Manulife\, the McLean Foundation\, and the Ka
 szas Group - BMO Nesbitt Burns.
LOCATION:Zoomerplex\, 70 Jefferson Avenue\, Toronto\, Ontario M6K 3H4
URL:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/stories-from-the-six-dd-at-doors-open-tick
 ets-45516089850
