BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Reimagining our History - DD at Doors Open
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20160528T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20160529T160000
UID:21258376376
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/reimagining-our-history-dd-at-door
 s-open-tickets-21258376376\n\nCanada's defining attributes are its multicu
 lturalism and inclusivity. Yet\, we tend to tell Canadian history through 
 the eyes of the white settler. For Doors Open 2016\, Diaspora Dialogues ha
 s invited some of the city's finest writers\, spoken word artists\, and pl
 aywrights to explore a moment or figure from Canadian history reimagined i
 n a more diverse and inclusive lens.\nReadings will take place from 10 a.m
 . to 4 p.m. in Old City Hall\, Court Room 121 for the duration of Doors Op
 en.\nFEATURING\n\nAlicia Elliott\nAmina Farah\nMia Herrera\nSheniz Janmoha
 med\nShaista Latif\nEdward Lee\nRabindranath Maharaj\nPasha Malla\nLee Mar
 acle\nSheila Murray\nPratap Reddy\nKerri Sakamoto\nShawn Salik\nPriscila U
 ppal\n\nHosted by:Dianah Smith\, writer\, teacher\, and arts educator.\nAn
 d more!
LOCATION:Old City Hall\, Court Room 121\, 60 Queen Street West\, Toronto\,
  Ontario M5H 2M3
URL:https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/reimagining-our-history-dd-at-doors-open-t
 ickets-21258376376
X-SOURCE:Diaspora Dialogues
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
